{
  "info": {
    "name": "Sniper Order Execution Engine",
    "description": "Single endpoint pattern: POST /api/orders/execute returns orderId, then upgrade to WebSocket for live updates",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Health Check",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "const response = pm.response.json();",
              "",
              "pm.test('Status code is 200', function() {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Service is healthy', function() {",
              "    pm.expect(response.status).to.equal('healthy');",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('All services connected', function() {",
              "    pm.expect(response.services.postgres).to.equal('connected');",
              "    pm.expect(response.services.redis).to.equal('connected');",
              "    pm.expect(response.services.queue).to.equal('running');",
              "});",
              "",
              "console.log('‚úÖ Health Status:', response.status);",
              "console.log('Services:', JSON.stringify(response.services, null, 2));"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "http://localhost:3000/health",
          "protocol": "http",
          "host": ["localhost"],
          "port": "3000",
          "path": ["health"]
        },
        "description": "‚úÖ START HERE: Check server health before testing\n\nVerifies:\n- PostgreSQL connection\n- Redis connection\n- BullMQ queue status"
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Submit Order (HTTP POST)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "const response = pm.response.json();",
              "",
              "pm.test('Status code is 200', function() {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response has orderId', function() {",
              "    pm.expect(response.orderId).to.be.a('string');",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Status is pending', function() {",
              "    pm.expect(response.status).to.equal('pending');",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response has upgradeUrl', function() {",
              "    pm.expect(response.upgradeUrl).to.be.a('string');",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Save orderId and upgradeUrl to environment",
              "pm.environment.set('orderId', response.orderId);",
              "pm.environment.set('upgradeUrl', response.upgradeUrl);",
              "",
              "console.log('‚úÖ Order ID:', response.orderId);",
              "console.log('üì° WebSocket URL:', response.upgradeUrl);",
              "console.log('');",
              "console.log('NEXT STEP: Use request #3 (WebSocket) to connect and see live updates!');"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"tokenAddress\": \"B2DdhSFkydrDMbeamxnVyxiZNABVPoTFJjZKzSc1G3DP\",\n  \"amountIn\": \"100000000\",\n  \"slippage\": \"0.01\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "http://localhost:3000/api/orders/execute",
          "protocol": "http",
          "host": ["localhost"],
          "port": "3000",
          "path": ["api", "orders", "execute"]
        },
        "description": "üìù STEP 1: Submit order via HTTP POST\n\nTask Requirement: \"User submits order via POST /api/orders/execute\"\n\n‚úÖ Returns orderId\n‚úÖ Returns upgradeUrl for WebSocket connection\n\nAfter running this request:\n1. Copy the upgradeUrl from response\n2. In Postman: New ‚Üí WebSocket Request\n3. Paste the upgradeUrl and Click 'Connect'\n4. Watch live status updates stream in real-time!\n\n‚è±Ô∏è Total execution: ~15-20 seconds\n\nüé¨ LIVE UPDATES YOU'LL SEE:\n- pending ‚Üí monitoring ‚Üí triggered ‚Üí routing (with DEX comparison) ‚Üí building ‚Üí submitted ‚Üí confirmed (with txHash)"
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Get Order Status (HTTP GET)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "const response = pm.response.json();",
              "",
              "pm.test('Status code is 200', function() {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Response has order details', function() {",
              "    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('id');",
              "    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('status');",
              "    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('token_address');",
              "});",
              "",
              "console.log('Order Status:', response.status);",
              "console.log('Token:', response.token_address);",
              "console.log('Amount:', response.amount_in);",
              "console.log('Selected DEX:', response.selected_dex);",
              "",
              "if (response.tx_hash) {",
              "    console.log('‚úÖ Transaction Hash:', response.tx_hash);",
              "    console.log('üîç Explorer:', 'https://explorer.solana.com/tx/' + response.tx_hash + '?cluster=devnet');",
              "}",
              "",
              "if (response.error_message) {",
              "    console.log('‚ùå Error:', response.error_message);",
              "}"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "http://localhost:3000/api/orders/{{orderId}}",
          "protocol": "http",
          "host": ["localhost"],
          "port": "3000",
          "path": ["api", "orders", "{{orderId}}"]
        },
        "description": "üìä STEP 2 (Optional): Check order status via HTTP\n\nUseful for:\n- Checking status after WebSocket disconnection\n- Retrieving transaction hash\n- Debugging failed orders\n\nReturns full order details from PostgreSQL"
      },
      "response": []
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "orderId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Order ID from POST request - automatically saved"
    },
    {
      "key": "upgradeUrl",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "WebSocket URL from POST request - automatically saved"
    }
  ],
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Sniper Order Execution Engine",
          "// Single endpoint: /api/orders/execute",
          "// HTTP POST ‚Üí returns orderId ‚Üí WebSocket upgrade for live updates"
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
}
